graphToNetwork(DirectedGraph, String[]) - Static method in class edu.missouri.bayesianConstructor.Main
Converts the given graph g into a BeliefNetwork displaced using a NodePlacer.GEOMETRIC configuration, placing each node in a different component All nodes in the new Belief Network are given the same set of possible values: those in the values parameter.
graphToNodeGraph(DirectedGraph, String[]) - Static method in class edu.missouri.bayesianConstructor.Main
Deprecated.
since version 0.05 (2016-03-20). A graph of nodes serves no other purpose than to create a edu.ucla.belief.BeliefNetwork; however, the graphs returned by this function are not fully supported by BeliefNetwork (Edges do not get updated properly). Use graphToNetwork(DirectedGraph, String[]) for this purpose instead.
